Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. Halve the @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise and widthwise, then cut into ½-inch spears), then cut into ½-inch spears (like pickles). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated). Grate the @shallot{1}(grated) into a #medium bowl{}. Peel and grate half the @cucumber{1}(peeled and grated, you'll need about 1/4 cup) into a #small bowl{}. Finely chop the @mint{¼%ounce}(finely chopped). Halve the @lemon{1}(halved).

Toss the zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place in the oven for ~{15-20%minutes}, flipping once, until golden brown. Finish with a squeeze of lemon over the top.

Make the meat mixture: Add the @ground beef{10%ounce}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, 1 Tablespoon yogurt, half the garlic, and half the mint to the #bowl{} with the shallot. Season with @salt{½%teaspoon} and @pepper{pinch}. Thoroughly combine and form into 4 oval logs.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the beef logs to the pan. Cook ~{3-4%minutes}, rotating to brown on all sides. Skewer each log lengthwise with @wooden skewers{4}. Place onto the baking sheet with the zucchini. Bake ~{10-12%minutes}, or until cooked through.

Cut the @whole wheat pitas{2}(cut into wedges) into wedges before tossing on a baking sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Bake about ~{10%minutes}, turning once, until golden brown and crispy.

> TIP: Check on the pita chips after 5 minutes to make sure they don't burn.

Make the tzatziki and serve: Add the remaining @yogurt{1} (plus a squeeze of lemon, the remaining mint, and a pinch of garlic (to taste)) to the bowl with the cucumber. Season with salt and pepper. Slice the remaining cucumber into half moons. Serve the gyro skewers, pita chips, cucumber slices, and roasted zucchini with the tzatziki for dipping. Enjoy!